Source: Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 58
Edition:
Quote: It was for a long time believed that a practicable inland communication between the northern end of this island and the country to the southward did not exist, and that the rugged Kaikoras [sic] formed a barrier from the sea on the east coast, to the great chain of Southern Alps which crown the west coast of the island from its northern to its southernmost end.
