Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: The Southern Alps in the Middle Island, form such a prominent feature in the landscape, that even the uncsientific traveller, when he passes along the west coast, cannot but admire their wild and fantastic forms, clad in a garment of snow, and standing boldly against the deep blue sky of New Zealand.
