Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: IT is not everyone who is privileged to have some portion of the country named after him, but such has been the reward of Arthur Dudley Dobson, civil engineer and pioneer, of Canterbury, after whom Arthur's Pass was named. Mr. Dobson was the first man to traverse the narrow by-pass which gives access from the Canterbury Plains to the narrow productive strip of Westland lying to the west of the Southern Alps.
